<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80951357EC1FD163ADCFEB2" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80951357EC1FD163ADCFEB2" blockId="9.[151,760,706,825]" lastBlockId="9.[828,1437,190,821]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80951357EC1FD163E4EFD3E" bold="true" box="[151,271,706,729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357FFDFD163D13FD3E" box="[427,594,706,729]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.825" metricValueMax="3.85" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="3.825" valueMax="3.85" valueMin="3.8">3.80–3.85 mm</quantity>
. antennomeres 9–11 each elongate, almost simple, antennomere 9 with small disc-like process near apex. Protrochanter with acute ventral spine, profemur with sharp spine at middle; mesotrochanter with acute ventral spine, mesotibia with small, blunt apical tubercle. Horn-like metaventral processes considerably short, apices truncate and bent downwards. Median lobe of aedeagus asymmetric; parameres short; endophallus composed of three sclerites. Female unknow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80951367D6AFE8A3EC7FE12" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80951367D6AFE8A3D1EFE32" blockId="9.[828,1437,190,821]" lastBlockId="10.[151,760,190,725]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80951357D6AFE8A3B42FE92" bold="true" box="[828,1027,350,373]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80951357D9DFE8A3B42FE92" bold="true" box="[971,1027,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Male</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357A46FE8A3B24FE92" box="[1040,1125,350,373]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[151,182,2061,2080]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,888,2037]" captionTargetId="figure-315@9.[210,1377,885,2042]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 7. Dorsal habitus of Pselaphodes males. A – P. jendeki sp. nov.; B – P. nongfa sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037482" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037482/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357AAAFE8A3AD8FE92" box="[1276,1433,350,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.825" metricValueMax="3.85" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="3.825" valueMax="3.85" valueMin="3.8">3.80–3.85 mm</quantity>
. Head slightly longer than wide, HL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357A93FEAA3A25FE72" box="[1221,1380,382,405]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.05" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="6.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.705" valueMax="0.73" valueMin="0.68">0.68–0.73 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357D6AFE4A3C9AFE52" box="[828,987,414,437]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8999999999999995" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.69" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.68">0.68–0.70 mm</quantity>
; eyes prominent, each composed of about 40 facets. Antennomeres 2–8 each moniliform, antennomeres 9–11 (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357D97FE0A3B53FE12" box="[961,1042,478,501]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) each strongly elongate and enlarged, antennomere 9 with small disc-like structure near apex. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357DE0FDCA3B4AFDD2" box="[950,1035,542,565]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as wide, PL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357D6AFDEA3C9AFDB2" box="[828,987,574,597]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.665" valueMax="0.68" valueMin="0.65">0.65–0.68 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357A4FFDEA3BF9FDB2" box="[1049,1208,574,597]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.45" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.645" valueMax="0.67" valueMin="0.62">0.62–0.67 mm</quantity>
, sides narrowing anteriorly at apical two-fifths. Elytra broader than long, EL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357D6AFDAA3C96FD72" box="[828,983,638,661]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.10–1.20 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80951357A58FDAA3BEBFD72" box="[1038,1194,638,661]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.30–1.40 mm</quantity>
. Horn-like metaventral processes (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357DFBFD4A3CBAFD52" box="[941,1019,670,693]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
) short and broad in lateral view, apically bifid, upper apex acute, apex truncate.Protrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357B27FD6A3C1CFD12" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
) with thin, acute ventral spine; profemur with sharp ventral spine at middle; mesotrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357B50FD2A3A1BFCF2" box="[1286,1370,766,789]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
) with acute ventral spine, mesofemur simple, mesotibia (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80951357B1EFCCA3AD4FCD2" box="[1352,1429,798,821]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
) with small apical tubercle; metatrochanters and metafemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80A51367EC9FF0A3FB5FF12" box="[159,244,222,245]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
) simple. Abdomen broad at base and narrowed apically, AL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80A51367F48FF2A3EFBFEF2" box="[286,442,254,277]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1749999999999998" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.15" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="1.1749999999999998" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.15">1.15–1.20 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80A51367FA5FF2A3D15FEF2" box="[499,596,254,277]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.30 mm</quantity>
. Sternite 7 (IX) (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80A51367EC9FECA3FB3FED2" box="[159,242,286,309]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
) hemi-membranous. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80A51367C1BFECA3DFAFED2" box="[589,699,286,309]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" captionTargetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" captionTargetId="figure-282@10.[269,1317,764,1996]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes jendeki sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Figs 8I–E</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80A51367C9FFECA3F81FEB2" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="0.75">0.75 mm</quantity>
long, median lobe asymmetric dorso-ventrally, narrowing apically and curved rightwards at apex in dorsal view; parameres much shorter than median lobe, each with three apical setae, endophallus composed of one triangle and two slightly curved, elongate sclerites.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF07DAF3E80951357EC1F7D93B7AF7C7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037482" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5037482" box="[151,1083,2061,2080]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037482/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" startId="9.[151,182,2061,2080]" targetBox="[213,1374,888,2037]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80951357EC1F7D93B7AF7C7" blockId="9.[151,1083,2061,2080]" box="[151,1083,2061,2080]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
